docs.lead_paragraph: The flooding from the Gowanus Canal has raised questions about inadequate infrastructure and filthy waters.

headline.seo: Gowanus Canal Flooding Brings Contamination Concerns
headline.main: In Brooklyn, Worrying About Not Only Flooding but Also What’s in Water
headline.print_headline: In Brooklyn, Worrying About Not Only Flooding But Also What’s in Water

docs.abstract: Elizabeth A Harris The Appraisal column discusses fact that floodwaters that poured from the Gowanus Canal into nearby South Brooklyn neighborhoods brought dangerous levels of contamination from the Superfund waterway; says concerns about inadequate infrastructure and filthy waters are especially pressing in the face of a great deal of looming development in the area.
docs.snippet: The flooding from the Gowanus Canal has raised questions about inadequate infrastructure and filthy waters.

docs.lead_paragraph: The judge said a business owner need not, at least for now, offer insurance coverage for contraceptives to employees because it infringes on his religious beliefs.

headline.seo: Judge Temporarily Blocks Mandate on Birth Control
headline.main: Michigan Judge Temporarily Blocks Health Law Mandate on Birth Control
headline.print_headline: Michigan Judge Temporarily Blocks Health Law Mandate on Birth Control

docs.abstract: Judge Robert H Cleland of Federal District Court in Detroit issues order shielding Weingartz Supply Co in Michigan from a requirement of health care law to provide insurance coverage for contraceptives at no charge to female employees; says requirement could infringe on the exercise of religious beliefs by owner Daniel Weingartz, and issues a preliminary injunction to stop the government from enforcing it.
docs.snippet: The judge said a business owner need not, at least for now, offer insurance coverage for contraceptives to employees because it infringes on his religious beliefs.
